        <trans-unit id="129" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Add a list:</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="130" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To number the list instead, use paired <ph id="ph1">\&lt;</ph>OL&gt; and <ph id="ph2">\&lt;</ph>/OL&gt; tags in place of the <ph id="ph3">\&lt;</ph>UL&gt; and <ph id="ph4">\&lt;</ph>/UL&gt; tags.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="131" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>That should get you started.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="132" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If you see a great feature on a Web page, you can find out how it was created by examining the HTML source.</source>
        </trans-unit>
